An urn contains marbles of five colors: red, white, blue, green, and yellow. When five marbles are drawn without replacement, the following events are equally likely:
(a) the selection of five red marbles;
(b) the selection of one white and four red marbles;
(c) the selection of one white, one blue, and three red marbles;
(d) the selection of one white, one blue, one green, and two red marbles;
(e) the selection of one marble of each color.
What is the smallest number of marbles satisfying the given condition?
A) 30
B) 33
C) 36
D) 39
E) More than 39

Abby, Bridget, and five of their classmates will be seated in two rows of four for a group photo. The seating arrangement is shown as follows:
\begin{eqnarray*} 
\text{X}&\quad\text{X}\quad&\text{X}&\quad\text{X} \\
\text{X}&\quad\text{X}\quad&\text{X}&\quad\text{X}  
\end{eqnarray*}
If the seating positions are assigned randomly, what is the probability that Abby and Bridget are directly next to each other either in the same row or the same column?
A) $\frac{1}{3}$  
B) $\frac{3}{7}$  
C) $\frac{5}{14}$  
D) $\frac{1}{2}$

Triangle $XYZ$ in the coordinate plane has vertices at the points $X(1, 0)$, $Y(0, 1)$, and $Z(-1, 0)$. Consider the following five transformations:
- $L$, a rotation of $120^\circ$ counterclockwise around the origin;
- $R$, a rotation of $120^\circ$ clockwise around the origin;
- $H$, a reflection across the $x$-axis;
- $V$, a reflection across the $y$-axis;
- $T$, a combination of a $120^\circ$ clockwise rotation followed by a reflection across the $y$-axis.
Each of these transformations maps the triangle onto itself, but the positions of the labeled vertices change. How many sequences of 24 transformations chosen from $\{L, R, H, V, T\}$ will send all the labeled vertices back to their original positions?
A) 810
B) 1365
C) 1820
D) 2380
E) 2860
